label: Accepted Name Usage
rdfs_comment: The full name, with authorship and date information if known, of the currently valid (zoological) or accepted (botanical) taxon.

label: Accepted Name Usage ID
rdfs_comment: An identifier for the name usage (documented meaning of the name according to a source) of the currently valid (zoological) or accepted (botanical) taxon.

label: Accepted Scientific Name
rdfs_comment: The currently valid (zoological) or accepted (botanical) name for the scientificName.
dcterms_description: Example: "Tamias minimus" valid name for "Eutamias minimus"

label: Accepted Scientific Name ID
rdfs_comment: A unique identifier for the acceptedScientificName.

label: Accepted Taxon
rdfs_comment: The currently valid (zoological) or accepted (botanical) name for the ScientificName.

label: Accepted Taxon ID
rdfs_comment: A global unique identifier for the parent to the AcceptedTaxon.

label: Accepted Taxon ID
rdfs_comment: An identifier for the name of the currently valid (zoological) or accepted (botanical) taxon. See acceptedTaxon.

label: Accepted Taxon Name
rdfs_comment: The currently valid (zoological) or accepted (botanical) name for the scientificName.
dcterms_description: Example: "Tamias minimus" valid name for "Eutamias minimus"

label: Accepted Taxon Name ID
rdfs_comment: A unique identifier for the acceptedTaxonName.

label: Access Constraints
rdfs_comment: A description of constraints on the use of the data as shared or access to further data that is not shared.
